});
ME.setAutoAdvance('Passage 2');
<</script>>\
<div class="passage-meta">Passage 1</div><div class="passage-scene">Waking</div>

One morning, when Gregor Samsa woke from troubled dreams, he found himself transformed in his bed into a horrible vermin. He <span class="lma" data-cat="effort" data-lma="Strong Weight, Sustained">lay</span> on his <span class="lma" data-cat="effort" data-lma="Strong Weight">armour-like</span> back, and if he <span class="lma" data-cat="shape" data-lma="Minimal Rise">lifted his head a little</span> he could see his brown belly, slightly domed and <span class="lma" data-cat="body" data-lma="Fragmented Connectivity">divided by arches into stiff sections</span>. The bedding was <span class="lma" data-cat="effort" data-lma="Strong Weight">hardly able to cover it</span> and seemed ready to slide off any moment. His many legs, <span class="lma" data-cat="body" data-lma="Low Connectivity">pitifully thin compared with the size of the rest of him</span>, <span class="lma" data-cat="effort" data-lma="Bound Flow">waved about helplessly</span> as he looked.

<div class="continue">[[Continue|Passage 2]]</div>

:: Passage 2 {"position":"300,350","size":"100,100"}
<<script>>
ME.triggerPassage(2, {
  passage_id: 2, action_drive: "press",
  flow: 0.15, intensity: 0.35, weight_passive: 0.0,
  shape_grow: 0.1, shape_rise: 0.0, shape_advance: 0.1,
  body_connectivity: 0.5, body_sequencing: 0.25,
  kinesphere: 0.35, space_approach: 0.85, space_plane: 0.25
});
ME.setAutoAdvance('Passage 3');
<</script>>\
<div class="passage-meta">Passage 2</div><div class="passage-scene">The room</div>

"What's happened to me?" he thought. It wasn't a dream. His room, a proper human room although a little too small, <span class="lma" data-cat="effort" data-lma="Sustained Time">lay peacefully</span> between its four familiar walls. A collection of textile samples lay spread out on the table and above it there hung a picture that he had recently cut out of an illustrated magazine and housed in a nice, gilded frame.

Gregor then <span class="lma" data-cat="shape" data-lma="Minimal Advance">turned to look out the window</span> at the dull weather. <span class="lma" data-cat="space" data-lma="Indirect, Free (environment)">Drops of rain could be heard hitting the pane</span>, which made him feel quite sad.

<div class="continue">[[Continue|Passage 3]]</div>

:: Passage 3 {"position":"300,500","size":"100,100"}
<<script>>
ME.triggerPassage(3, {
  passage_id: 3, action_drive: "press",
  flow: 0.2, intensity: 0.55, weight_passive: 0.0,
  shape_grow: 0.15, shape_rise: 0.1, shape_advance: 0.1,
  body_connectivity: 0.45, body_sequencing: 0.35,
  kinesphere: 0.35, space_approach: 0.8, space_plane: 0.3
});
ME.setAutoAdvance('Passage 4');
<</script>>\
<div class="passage-meta">Passage 3</div><div class="passage-scene">Anxiety about work</div>

"How about if I sleep a little bit longer and forget all this nonsense," he thought, but that was something he was unable to do because he was used to sleeping on his right, and in his present state couldn't get into that position. However hard he <span class="lma" data-cat="effort" data-lma="Strong Weight, Sudden burst">threw himself onto his right</span>, he always <span class="lma" data-cat="shape" data-lma="Failed Advance">rolled back to where he was</span>.

"Oh, God," he thought, "what a strenuous career it is that I've chosen! It can all go to Hell!" He felt a slight itch up on his belly; <span class="lma" data-cat="effort" data-lma="Strong Weight, Sustained">pushed himself slowly up</span> on his back towards the headboard so that he could lift his head better; found where the itch was, and saw that it was covered with lots of little white spots which he didn't know what to make of; and when he tried to feel the place with one of his legs he <span class="lma" data-cat="effort" data-lma="Sudden Time">drew it quickly back</span> because as soon as he touched it he was overcome by a <span class="lma" data-cat="body" data-lma="Involuntary response">cold shudder</span>.

<div class="continue">[[Continue|Passage 4]]</div>

:: Passage 4 {"position":"300,650","size":"100,100"}
<<script>>
ME.triggerPassage(4, {
  passage_id: 4, action_drive: "press",
  flow: 0.25, intensity: 0.65, weight_passive: 0.0,
  shape_grow: 0.15, shape_rise: 0.15, shape_advance: 0.2,
  body_connectivity: 0.45, body_sequencing: 0.3,
  kinesphere: 0.4, space_approach: 0.75, space_plane: 0.3
});
ME.setAutoAdvance('Passage 5');
<</script>>\
<div class="passage-meta">Passage 4</div><div class="passage-scene">Clock strikes, mother knocks</div>

And he looked over at the alarm clock, <span class="lma" data-cat="space" data-lma="Sustained, Bound (environment)">ticking</span> on the chest of drawers. "God in Heaven!" he thought. It was half past six and the hands were <span class="lma" data-cat="effort" data-lma="Sustained Time">quietly moving forwards</span>, it was even later than half past, more like quarter to seven. Had the alarm clock not rung?

He was still hurriedly thinking all this through, <span class="lma" data-cat="effort" data-lma="Bound Flow">unable to decide to get out of the bed</span>, when the clock struck quarter to seven. There was a <span class="lma" data-cat="effort" data-lma="Sudden, Direct (external)">cautious knock</span> at the door near his head. "Gregor," somebody called. It was his mother. "It's quarter to seven. Didn't you want to go somewhere?"

<div class="continue">[[Continue|Passage 5]]</div>

:: Passage 5 {"position":"300,800","size":"100,100"}
<<script>>
ME.triggerPassage(5, {
  passage_id: 5, action_drive: "wring",
  flow: 0.3, intensity: 0.75, weight_passive: 0.0,
  shape_grow: 0.15, shape_rise: 0.2, shape_advance: 0.3,
  body_connectivity: 0.4, body_sequencing: 0.4,
  kinesphere: 0.4, space_approach: 0.5, space_plane: 0.3
});
ME.setAutoAdvance('Passage 6');
<</script>>\
<div class="passage-meta">Passage 5</div><div class="passage-scene">Trying to speak</div>

Gregor was <span class="lma" data-cat="effort" data-lma="Sudden Time">shocked</span> when he heard his own voice answering, it could hardly be recognised as the voice he had had before. As if from deep inside him, there was a <span class="lma" data-cat="body" data-lma="Loss of Connectivity">painful and uncontrollable squeaking</span> mixed in with it, the words could be made out at first but then there was a <span class="lma" data-cat="space" data-lma="Indirect Space">sort of echo which made them unclear</span>, leaving the hearer unsure whether he had heard properly or not.

Gregor had wanted to give a full answer and explain everything, but in the circumstances contented himself with saying: "Yes, mother, yes, thank-you, I'm getting up now."

<div class="continue">[[Continue|Passage 6]]</div>

:: Passage 6 {"position":"300,950","size":"100,100"}
<<script>>
ME.triggerPassage(6, {
  passage_id: 6, action_drive: "press",
  flow: 0.2, intensity: 0.8, weight_passive: 0.0,
  shape_grow: 0.2, shape_rise: 0.2, shape_advance: 0.5,
  body_connectivity: 0.35, body_sequencing: 0.45,
  kinesphere: 0.45, space_approach: 0.7, space_plane: 0.4
});
ME.setAutoAdvance('Passage 7');
<</script>>\
<div class="passage-meta">Passage 6</div><div class="passage-scene">Getting out of bed</div>

It was a simple matter to throw off the covers; he only had to <span class="lma" data-cat="shape" data-lma="Grow">blow himself up a little</span> and they fell off by themselves. But it became difficult after that, especially as he was so <span class="lma" data-cat="shape" data-lma="Lateral presence">exceptionally broad</span>. He would have used his arms and his hands to push himself up; but instead of them he only had all those <span class="lma" data-cat="effort" data-lma="Bound Flow, Indirect Space">little legs continuously moving in different directions</span>, and which he was moreover <span class="lma" data-cat="body" data-lma="Loss of Connectivity">unable to control</span>.

The first thing he wanted to do was get the lower part of his body out of the bed, but he had <span class="lma" data-cat="body" data-lma="Fragmented Connectivity">never seen this lower part, and could not imagine what it looked like</span>; it turned out to be too hard to move; it went so slowly; and finally, almost in a frenzy, when he <span class="lma" data-cat="effort" data-lma="Strong Weight, maximum force">carelessly shoved himself forwards with all the force he could gather</span>, he chose the wrong direction, <span class="lma" data-cat="effort" data-lma="Sudden, Strong, Direct">hit hard against the lower bedpost</span>, and learned from the <span class="lma" data-cat="body" data-lma="Sensory feedback">burning pain</span> he felt that the lower part of his body might well, at present, be the most sensitive.

<div class="continue">[[Continue|Passage 7]]</div>

:: Passage 7 {"position":"300,1100","size":"100,100"}
